meeting-rooms-iii.examples:
n = 2, meetings = [[0,10],[1,5],[2,7],[3,4]]
1. Meeting [0,10]: Room 0 available. Assign to Room 0. Room 0 busy until 10. Counts: {0:1, 1:0}
2. Meeting [1,5]: Room 1 available. Assign to Room 1. Room 1 busy until 5. Counts: {0:1, 1:1}
3. Meeting [2,7]: Both rooms busy. Room 1 frees at 5 (earlier). Delay meeting to start at 5. Assign to Room 1. Room 1 busy until 5 + (7-2) = 10. Counts: {0:1, 1:2}
4. Meeting [3,4]: Both rooms busy. Both free at 10. Room 0 has smaller index. Delay meeting to start at 10. Assign to Room 0. Room 0 busy until 10 + (4-3) = 11. Counts: {0:2, 1:2}
Both rooms hosted 2 meetings. Room 0 has the smallest index.
Output: 0
